151// TType implementation.
152TType::TType() : TType(EbtVoid, 0, 0) {}
153
154TType::TType(TBasicType t, unsigned char ps, unsigned char ss)
155 : TType(t, EbpUndefined, EvqGlobal, ps, ss)
156{}
157
158TType::TType(TBasicType t, TPrecision p, TQualifier q, unsigned char ps, unsigned char ss)
159 : TType(t, p, q, ps, ss, TSpan<const unsigned int>(), nullptr)
160{}
161
162TType::TType(const TPublicType &p)
163 : type(p.getBasicType()),
164 precision(p.precision),
165 qualifier(p.qualifier),
166 invariant(p.invariant),
167 precise(p.precise),
168 memoryQualifier(p.memoryQualifier),
169 layoutQualifier(p.layoutQualifier),
170 primarySize(p.getPrimarySize()),
171 secondarySize(p.getSecondarySize()),
172 mArraySizesStorage(nullptr),
173 mInterfaceBlock(nullptr),
174 mStructure(nullptr),
175 mIsStructSpecifier(false),
176 mMangledName(nullptr)
177{
178 ASSERT(primarySize <= 4);
179 ASSERT(secondarySize <= 4);
180 if (p.isArray())
181 {
182 makeArrays(*p.arraySizes);
183 }
184 if (p.getUserDef())
185 {
186 mStructure = p.getUserDef();
187 mIsStructSpecifier = p.isStructSpecifier();
188 }
189}
190
191TType::TType(const TStructure *userDef, bool isStructSpecifier)
192 : TType(EbtStruct, EbpUndefined, EvqTemporary, 1, 1)
193{
194 mStructure = userDef;
195 mIsStructSpecifier = isStructSpecifier;
196}

198TType::TType(const TInterfaceBlock *interfaceBlockIn,
199 TQualifier qualifierIn,
200 TLayoutQualifier layoutQualifierIn)
201 : TType(EbtInterfaceBlock, EbpUndefined, qualifierIn, 1, 1)
202{
203 layoutQualifier = layoutQualifierIn;
204 mInterfaceBlock = interfaceBlockIn;
205}

207TType::TType(const TType &t)
208{
209 *this = t;
210}
211
212TType &TType::operator=(const TType &t)
213{
214 type = t.type;
215 precision = t.precision;
216 qualifier = t.qualifier;
217 invariant = t.invariant;
218 precise = t.precise;
219 memoryQualifier = t.memoryQualifier;
220 layoutQualifier = t.layoutQualifier;
221 primarySize = t.primarySize;
222 secondarySize = t.secondarySize;
223 mArraySizesStorage = nullptr;
224 mInterfaceBlock = t.mInterfaceBlock;
225 mStructure = t.mStructure;
226 mIsStructSpecifier = t.mIsStructSpecifier;
227 mMangledName = t.mMangledName;
228
229 if (t.mArraySizesStorage)
230 {
231 // If other type has storage, duplicate the storage and set the view to our own storage.
232 mArraySizesStorage = new TVector<unsigned int>(*t.mArraySizesStorage);
233 mArraySizes = *mArraySizesStorage;
234 }
235 else
236 {
237 // Otherwise reference the same (constexpr) array sizes as the other type.
238 mArraySizes = t.mArraySizes;
239 }
240
241 return *this;
242}

244bool TType::canBeConstructed() const
245{
246 switch (type)
247 {
248 case EbtFloat:
249 case EbtInt:
250 case EbtUInt:
251 case EbtBool:
252 case EbtStruct:
253 return true;
254 default:
255 return false;
256 }
257}

259const char *TType::getBuiltInTypeNameString() const
260{
261 if (isMatrix())
262 {
263 switch (getCols())
264 {
265 case 2:
266 switch (getRows())
267 {
268 case 2:
269 return "mat2";
270 case 3:
271 return "mat2x3";
272 case 4:
273 return "mat2x4";
274 default:
275 UNREACHABLE();
276 return nullptr;
277 }
278 case 3:
279 switch (getRows())
280 {
281 case 2:
282 return "mat3x2";
283 case 3:
284 return "mat3";
285 case 4:
286 return "mat3x4";
287 default:
288 UNREACHABLE();
289 return nullptr;
290 }
291 case 4:
292 switch (getRows())
293 {
294 case 2:
295 return "mat4x2";
296 case 3:
297 return "mat4x3";
298 case 4:
299 return "mat4";
300 default:
301 UNREACHABLE();
302 return nullptr;
303 }
304 default:
305 UNREACHABLE();
306 return nullptr;
307 }
308 }
309 if (isVector())
310 {
311 switch (getBasicType())
312 {
313 case EbtFloat:
314 switch (getNominalSize())
315 {
316 case 2:
317 return "vec2";
318 case 3:
319 return "vec3";
320 case 4:
321 return "vec4";
322 default:
323 UNREACHABLE();
324 return nullptr;
325 }
326 case EbtInt:
327 switch (getNominalSize())
328 {
329 case 2:
330 return "ivec2";
331 case 3:
332 return "ivec3";
333 case 4:
334 return "ivec4";
335 default:
336 UNREACHABLE();
337 return nullptr;
338 }
339 case EbtBool:
340 switch (getNominalSize())
341 {
342 case 2:
343 return "bvec2";
344 case 3:
345 return "bvec3";
346 case 4:
347 return "bvec4";
348 default:
349 UNREACHABLE();
350 return nullptr;
351 }
352 case EbtUInt:
353 switch (getNominalSize())
354 {
355 case 2:
356 return "uvec2";
357 case 3:
358 return "uvec3";
359 case 4:
360 return "uvec4";
361 default:
362 UNREACHABLE();
363 return nullptr;
364 }
365 default:
366 UNREACHABLE();
367 return nullptr;
368 }
369 }
370 ASSERT(getBasicType() != EbtStruct);
371 ASSERT(getBasicType() != EbtInterfaceBlock);
372 return getBasicString();
373}

405bool TType::canReplaceWithConstantUnion() const
406{
407 if (isArray())
408 {
409 return false;
410 }
411 if (!mStructure)
412 {
413 return true;
414 }
415 if (isStructureContainingArrays())
416 {
417 return false;
418 }
419 if (getObjectSize() > 16)
420 {
421 return false;
422 }
423 return true;
424}

426//
427// Recursively generate mangled names.
428//
429const char *TType::buildMangledName() const
430{
431 TString mangledName(1, GetSizeMangledName(primarySize, secondarySize));
432
433 TBasicMangledName typeName(type);
434 char *basicMangledName = typeName.getName();
435 static_assert(TBasicMangledName::mangledNameSize == 2, "Mangled name size is not 2");
436 if (basicMangledName[0] != '{')
437 {
438 mangledName += basicMangledName[0];
439 mangledName += basicMangledName[1];
440 }
441 else
442 {
443 ASSERT(type == EbtStruct || type == EbtInterfaceBlock);
444 switch (type)
445 {
446 case EbtStruct:
447 mangledName += "{s";
448 if (mStructure->symbolType() != SymbolType::Empty)
449 {
450 mangledName += mStructure->name().data();
451 }
452 mangledName += mStructure->mangledFieldList();
453 mangledName += '}';
454 break;
455 case EbtInterfaceBlock:
456 mangledName += "{i";
457 mangledName += mInterfaceBlock->name().data();
458 mangledName += mInterfaceBlock->mangledFieldList();
459 mangledName += '}';
460 break;
461 default:
462 UNREACHABLE();
463 break;
464 }
465 }
466
467 for (unsigned int arraySize : mArraySizes)
468 {
469 char buf[20];
470 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%d", arraySize);
471 mangledName += 'x';
472 mangledName += buf;
473 }
474
475 // Copy string contents into a pool-allocated buffer, so we never need to call delete.
476 return AllocatePoolCharArray(mangledName.c_str(), mangledName.size());
477}
478
479size_t TType::getObjectSize() const
480{
481 size_t totalSize;
482
483 if (getBasicType() == EbtStruct)
484 totalSize = mStructure->objectSize();
485 else
486 totalSize = primarySize * secondarySize;
487
488 if (totalSize == 0)
489 return 0;
490
491 for (size_t arraySize : mArraySizes)
492 {
493 if (arraySize > INT_MAX / totalSize)
494 totalSize = INT_MAX;
495 else
496 totalSize *= arraySize;
497 }
498
499 return totalSize;
500}
501
502int TType::getLocationCount() const
503{
504 int count = 1;
505
506 if (getBasicType() == EbtStruct)
507 {
508 count = mStructure->getLocationCount();
509 }
510
511 if (count == 0)
512 {
513 return 0;
514 }
515
516 for (unsigned int arraySize : mArraySizes)
517 {
518 if (arraySize > static_cast<unsigned int>(std::numeric_limits<int>::max() / count))
519 {
520 count = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
521 }
522 else
523 {
524 count *= static_cast<int>(arraySize);
525 }
526 }
527
528 return count;
529}
530
531unsigned int TType::getArraySizeProduct() const
532{
533 unsigned int product = 1u;
534
535 for (unsigned int arraySize : mArraySizes)
536 {
537 product *= arraySize;
538 }
539 return product;
540}
541
542bool TType::isUnsizedArray() const
543{
544 for (unsigned int arraySize : mArraySizes)
545 {
546 if (arraySize == 0u)
547 {
548 return true;
549 }
550 }
551 return false;
552}
553
554bool TType::sameNonArrayType(const TType &right) const
555{
556 return (type == right.type && primarySize == right.primarySize &&
557 secondarySize == right.secondarySize && mStructure == right.mStructure);
558}
559
560bool TType::isElementTypeOf(const TType &arrayType) const
561{
562 if (!sameNonArrayType(arrayType))
563 {
564 return false;
565 }
566 if (arrayType.getNumArraySizes() != getNumArraySizes() + 1u)
567 {
568 return false;
569 }
570 for (size_t i = 0; i < mArraySizes.size(); ++i)
571 {
572 if (mArraySizes[i] != arrayType.mArraySizes[i])
573 {
574 return false;
575 }
576 }
577 return true;
578}
579
580void TType::sizeUnsizedArrays(const TSpan<const unsigned int> &newArraySizes)
581{
582 ASSERT(!isArray() || mArraySizesStorage != nullptr);
583 for (size_t i = 0u; i < getNumArraySizes(); ++i)
584 {
585 if (mArraySizes[i] == 0)
586 {
587 if (i < newArraySizes.size())
588 {
589 (*mArraySizesStorage)[i] = newArraySizes[i];
590 }
591 else
592 {
593 (*mArraySizesStorage)[i] = 1u;
594 }
595 }
596 }
597 invalidateMangledName();
598}
599
600void TType::sizeOutermostUnsizedArray(unsigned int arraySize)
601{
602 ASSERT(isArray() && mArraySizesStorage != nullptr);
603 ASSERT((*mArraySizesStorage).back() == 0u);
604 (*mArraySizesStorage).back() = arraySize;
605}

636void TType::makeArray(unsigned int s)
637{
638 if (mArraySizesStorage == nullptr)
639 {
640 mArraySizesStorage = new TVector<unsigned int>();
641 }
642 // Add a dimension to the current ones.
643 mArraySizesStorage->push_back(s);
644 onArrayDimensionsChange(*mArraySizesStorage);
645}
646
647void TType::makeArrays(const TSpan<const unsigned int> &sizes)
648{
649 if (mArraySizesStorage == nullptr)
650 {
651 mArraySizesStorage = new TVector<unsigned int>();
652 }
653 // Add dimensions to the current ones.
654 mArraySizesStorage->insert(mArraySizesStorage->end(), sizes.begin(), sizes.end());
655 onArrayDimensionsChange(*mArraySizesStorage);
656}
657
658void TType::setArraySize(size_t arrayDimension, unsigned int s)
659{
660 ASSERT(isArray() && mArraySizesStorage != nullptr);
661 ASSERT(arrayDimension < mArraySizesStorage->size());
662 if (mArraySizes[arrayDimension] != s)
663 {
664 (*mArraySizesStorage)[arrayDimension] = s;
665 invalidateMangledName();
666 }
667}
668
669void TType::toArrayElementType()
670{
671 ASSERT(isArray() && mArraySizesStorage != nullptr);
672 mArraySizesStorage->pop_back();
673 onArrayDimensionsChange(*mArraySizesStorage);
674}
675
676void TType::toArrayBaseType()
677{
678 if (!isArray())
679 {
680 return;
681 }
682 if (mArraySizesStorage)
683 {
684 mArraySizesStorage->clear();
685 }
686 onArrayDimensionsChange(TSpan<const unsigned int>());
687}

712
713void TType::createSamplerSymbols(const ImmutableString &namePrefix,
714 const TString &apiNamePrefix,
715 TVector<const TVariable *> *outputSymbols,
716 TMap<const TVariable *, TString> *outputSymbolsToAPINames,
717 TSymbolTable *symbolTable) const
718{
719 if (isStructureContainingSamplers())
720 {
721 if (isArray())
722 {
723 TType elementType(*this);
724 elementType.toArrayElementType();
725 for (unsigned int arrayIndex = 0u; arrayIndex < getOutermostArraySize(); ++arrayIndex)
726 {
727 std::stringstream elementName = sh::InitializeStream<std::stringstream>();
728 elementName << namePrefix << "_" << arrayIndex;
729 TStringStream elementApiName;
730 elementApiName << apiNamePrefix << "[" << arrayIndex << "]";
731 elementType.createSamplerSymbols(ImmutableString(elementName.str()),
732 elementApiName.str(), outputSymbols,
733 outputSymbolsToAPINames, symbolTable);
734 }
735 }
736 else
737 {
738 mStructure->createSamplerSymbols(namePrefix.data(), apiNamePrefix, outputSymbols,
739 outputSymbolsToAPINames, symbolTable);
740 }
741 return;
742 }
743
744 ASSERT(IsSampler(type));
745 TVariable *variable =
746 new TVariable(symbolTable, namePrefix, new TType(*this), SymbolType::AngleInternal);
747 outputSymbols->push_back(variable);
748 if (outputSymbolsToAPINames)
749 {
750 (*outputSymbolsToAPINames)[variable] = apiNamePrefix;
751 }
752}

754TFieldListCollection::TFieldListCollection(const TFieldList *fields)
755 : mFields(fields), mObjectSize(0), mDeepestNesting(0)
756{}
757
758bool TFieldListCollection::containsArrays() const
759{
760 for (const auto *field : *mFields)
761 {
762 const TType *fieldType = field->type();
763 if (fieldType->isArray() || fieldType->isStructureContainingArrays())
764 return true;
765 }
766 return false;
767}
768
769bool TFieldListCollection::containsMatrices() const
770{
771 for (const auto *field : *mFields)
772 {
773 const TType *fieldType = field->type();
774 if (fieldType->isMatrix() || fieldType->isStructureContainingMatrices())
775 return true;
776 }
777 return false;
778}
779
780bool TFieldListCollection::containsType(TBasicType type) const
781{
782 for (const auto *field : *mFields)
783 {
784 const TType *fieldType = field->type();
785 if (fieldType->getBasicType() == type || fieldType->isStructureContainingType(type))
786 return true;
787 }
788 return false;
789}
790
791bool TFieldListCollection::containsSamplers() const
792{
793 for (const auto *field : *mFields)
794 {
795 const TType *fieldType = field->type();
796 if (IsSampler(fieldType->getBasicType()) || fieldType->isStructureContainingSamplers())
797 return true;
798 }
799 return false;
800}
801
802TString TFieldListCollection::buildMangledFieldList() const
803{
804 TString mangledName;
805 for (const auto *field : *mFields)
806 {
807 mangledName += field->type()->getMangledName();
808 }
809 return mangledName;
810}
811
812size_t TFieldListCollection::calculateObjectSize() const
813{
814 size_t size = 0;
815 for (const TField *field : *mFields)
816 {
817 size_t fieldSize = field->type()->getObjectSize();
818 if (fieldSize > INT_MAX - size)
819 size = INT_MAX;
820 else
821 size += fieldSize;
822 }
823 return size;
824}
825
826size_t TFieldListCollection::objectSize() const
827{
828 if (mObjectSize == 0)
829 mObjectSize = calculateObjectSize();
830 return mObjectSize;
831}
832
833int TFieldListCollection::getLocationCount() const
834{
835 int count = 0;
836 for (const TField *field : *mFields)
837 {
838 int fieldCount = field->type()->getLocationCount();
839 if (fieldCount > std::numeric_limits<int>::max() - count)
840 {
841 count = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
842 }
843 else
844 {
845 count += fieldCount;
846 }
847 }
848 return count;
849}
850
851int TFieldListCollection::deepestNesting() const
852{
853 if (mDeepestNesting == 0)
854 mDeepestNesting = calculateDeepestNesting();
855 return mDeepestNesting;
856}
857
858const TString &TFieldListCollection::mangledFieldList() const
859{
860 if (mMangledFieldList.empty())
861 mMangledFieldList = buildMangledFieldList();
862 return mMangledFieldList;
863}
864
865int TFieldListCollection::calculateDeepestNesting() const
866{
867 int maxNesting = 0;
868 for (size_t i = 0; i < mFields->size(); ++i)
869 maxNesting = std::max(maxNesting, (*mFields)[i]->type()->getDeepestStructNesting());
870 return 1 + maxNesting;
871}

873// TPublicType implementation.
874void TPublicType::initialize(const TTypeSpecifierNonArray &typeSpecifier, TQualifier q)
875{
876 typeSpecifierNonArray = typeSpecifier;
877 layoutQualifier = TLayoutQualifier::Create();
878 memoryQualifier = TMemoryQualifier::Create();
879 qualifier = q;
880 invariant = false;
881 precise = false;
882 precision = EbpUndefined;
883 arraySizes = nullptr;
884}
885
886void TPublicType::initializeBasicType(TBasicType basicType)
887{
888 typeSpecifierNonArray.type = basicType;
889 typeSpecifierNonArray.primarySize = 1;
890 typeSpecifierNonArray.secondarySize = 1;
891 layoutQualifier = TLayoutQualifier::Create();
892 memoryQualifier = TMemoryQualifier::Create();
893 qualifier = EvqTemporary;
894 invariant = false;
895 precise = false;
896 precision = EbpUndefined;
897 arraySizes = nullptr;
898}
899
900bool TPublicType::isStructureContainingArrays() const
901{
902 if (!typeSpecifierNonArray.userDef)
903 {
904 return false;
905 }
906
907 return typeSpecifierNonArray.userDef->containsArrays();
908}
909
910bool TPublicType::isStructureContainingType(TBasicType t) const
911{
912 if (!typeSpecifierNonArray.userDef)
913 {
914 return false;
915 }
916
917 return typeSpecifierNonArray.userDef->containsType(t);
918}

920void TPublicType::setArraySizes(TVector<unsigned int> *sizes)
921{
922 arraySizes = sizes;
923}
924
925bool TPublicType::isArray() const
926{
927 return arraySizes && !arraySizes->empty();
928}
929
930void TPublicType::clearArrayness()
931{
932 arraySizes = nullptr;
933}
934
935bool TPublicType::isAggregate() const
936{
937 return isArray() || typeSpecifierNonArray.isMatrix() || typeSpecifierNonArray.isVector();
938}
